column1: Albert Einstein is a scientist. Albert Einstein's death date is 18 April 1955. His birth date is 14 March 1879, his birth places are Kingdom of Württemberg, German Empire and Ulm and his alma maters are University of Zurich and ETH Zurich. He is known for, among others, Brownian motion, Gravitational wave, Special relativity, EPR paradox and General relativity. His fields are Physics and Philosophy.

Michael Jackson is a musical artist. His active years start year is 01 January 1964 and his genres are, among others, Rock music, Soul music, Dance - pop, Pop music and Disco. His background is "solo singer". He is associated band The Jackson 5 and The Jackson 5. Michael Jackson's record labels are, among others, MJJ Music, Sony Music Entertainment, Motown, Legacy Recordings and Epic Records.

Barack Obama is an office holder. Barack Obama's birth places are Honolulu and Hawaii, its office is "44thPresident of the United States" and its birth date is 04 August 1961. Its term periods are Barack Obama  1, Barack Obama  2 and Barack Obama  3, its successors are Roland Burris and Kwame Raoul, its predecessors are George W . Bush, Alice Palmer and Peter Fitzgerald and its party is Democratic Party.

Angela Merkel is an office holder. Her birth places are West Germany and Hamburg, her offices are "Minister for Women and Youth", "Minister for the Environment", "Chancellor of Germany" and "Leader of the Christian Democratic Union of Germany", her birth year is 01 January 1954 and her birth date is 17 July 1954. Angela Merkel's term periods are Angela Merkel  1, Angela Merkel  2, Angela Merkel  3 and Angela Merkel  4, her alma mater is Leipzig University, her successors are Claudia Nolte and Jürgen Trittin, her predecessors are Klaus Töpfer, Federal Ministry of Family Affairs, Senior Citizens, Women and Youth, Gerhard Schröder and Wolfgang Schäuble and her parties are Christian Democratic Union of Germany and Democratic Awakening.
